$AMBERHOME/bin/tleap -f leaprc.protein.ff14SB
source leaprc.gaff
source leaprc.water.tip3p

----------------then solvent specific parameter files-----------
#Pyrimidine
loadamberprep Pyrimidine_JJ_AMBER.prepi
loadamberparams Pyrimidine_JJ_AMBERw.frcmod
1P3=loadpdb Pyrimidine_W_Equ.pdb

#N-methylacetamide
loadamberprep NMA_oplsaaJ.prepi
loadamberparams NMA_oplsaaJ.frcmod
NMA=loadpdb Jorg-newBoxnmanpt.rst.pdb

#Acetonitrile
loadamberprep acetonitrile.prepi
loadamberparams acetonitrile.frcmod
C3N=loadpdb ACNbox.prmpdb

#Isopropyl alcohol
loadamberprep JorgAA_IPAnb.prepi
loadamberparams JorgAA_IPAnb.frcmod
IPA=loadpdb JorgAA_IPAbox.pdb

#Methylammonium/Acetate mix
loadamberprep MAI.prepi
loadamberparams MAI.frcmod
loadamberprep ACT.prepi
loadamberparams ACT.frcmod
AMA=loadpdb ACTMAI_eqbox.pdb

#Imidazole
loadamberprep Imidazole_JJ_AMBER.prepi
loadamberparams Imidazole_JJ_AMBERw.frcmod
IMI=loadpdb Imidazole_W_Equ.pdb

----------------------

set AMA restype solvent   #Change AMA to name of solvent you are using
setbox AMA centers        
prot=loadpdb protein.pdb
solvateshell prot AMA 9.6  
savepdb prot prot_nowater.pdb
saveamberparm prot_nowater.prmtop prot_nowater.inpcrd
solvatebox prot TIP3PBOX 10    
savepdb prot prot_solvated.pdb

Ratios for 5%/95% v/v probe to water
1 IMI: 69.7 waters
1 NMA: 80.62 waters
1 ACN: 55.07 waters
1 IPA: 80.62 waters
1 ACT: 118.6 waters
1 1P3: 83.11 waters

There are two possible ways to get the correct ratio that I've used:
1) Use constant thickness of probes, ex. 9.6, and then vary the thickness of the water layer
2) Determine how many waters you would add normally, calculate how many probes you want, and then vary probe layer.

When solvating with the charged probes (ACT/MAI), equal numbers of each are not necessarily added.  I save an intermediate pdb, delete how ever many are necessary to get a net neutral charge, and then reload this into tleap.




